        -:  148:/*  According to the shape/flags of the matrix we have to distinghish 3 different cases:
        -:  149: *   1 - the matrix is col-major, BLAS compatible and M is large => call fast BLAS-like colmajor routine
        -:  150: *   2 - the matrix is row-major, BLAS compatible and N is large => call fast BLAS-like rowmajor routine
        -:  151: *   3 - all other cases are handled using a simple loop along the outer-storage direction.
        -:  152: *  Therefore we need a lower level meta selector.
        -:  153: *  Furthermore, if the matrix is the rhs, then the product has to be transposed.
        -:  154: */
